},"’":{"docs":{},"df":0,"l":{"docs":{},"df":0,"l":{"docs":{"https://nixthe.systems/docs/":{"tf":1.0},"https://nixthe.systems/docs/installing-nixos-on-vps/":{"tf":1.4142135623730951}},"df":2}}}}}}}},"title":{"root":{"docs":{},"df":0,"c":{"docs":{},"df":0,"o":{"docs":{},"df":0,"n":{"docs":{},"df":0,"f":{"docs":{},"df":0,"i":{"docs":{},"df":0,"g":{"docs":{},"df":0,"u":{"docs":{},"df":0,"r":{"docs":{"https://nixthe.systems/configurations/":{"tf":1.0}},"df":1}}}}}}}},"h":{"docs":{},"df":0,"o":{"docs":{},"df":0,"m":{"docs":{},"df":0,"e":{"docs":{"https://nixthe.systems/":{"tf":1.0}},"df":1}}}},"i":{"docs":{},"df":0,"n":{"docs":{},"df":0,"s":{"docs":{},"df":0,"t":{"docs":{},"df":0,"a":{"docs":{},"df":0,"l":{"docs":{"https://nixthe.systems/docs/installing-nixos-on-vps/":{"tf":1.0}},"df":1}}}}}},"n":{"docs":{},"df":0,"i":{"docs":{},"df":0,"x":{"docs":{"https://nixthe.systems/about/":{"tf":1.0},"https://nixthe.systems/docs/":{"tf":1.0}},"df":2,"o":{"docs":{"https://nixthe.systems/docs/installing-nixos-on-vps/":{"tf":1.0}},"df":1}}}},"s":{"docs":{},"df":0,"y":{"docs":{},"df":0,"s":{"docs":{},"df":0,"t":{"docs":{},"df":0,"e":{"docs":{},"df":0,"m":{"docs":{"https://nixthe.systems/about/":{"tf":1.0},"https://nixthe.systems/docs/":{"tf":1.0}},"df":2}}}}}},"v":{"docs":{},"df":0,"p":{"docs":{"https://nixthe.systems/docs/installing-nixos-on-vps/":{"tf":1.0}},"df":1}}}}},"documentStore":{"save":true,"docs":{"https://nixthe.systems/":{"body":"\nNix the Systems\nDiscover and share Nix configurations, documentations and more.\n","id":"https://nixthe.systems/","title":"Home"},"https://nixthe.systems/about/":{"body":"Welcome, everyone!\nThank you for joining us today. I will be brief and get straight to the point about the purpose of this initiative and the inspiration behind it.\nI have a deep appreciation for NIX and use it daily whenever possible. My goal was to create a platform that consolidates various NIX configurations, offering inspiration and resources for building upon them. Noticing a gap in this area, I took the initiative to develop this project, and here we are.\nWhat to Expect from Us\nWe are here to assist you with your Nix and NixOS challenges, offering both free and paid support.\nDonations\nWe welcome and appreciate any donations to support this project. Your contributions, whether through code or financial support, will help us manage and sustain our efforts.\nIn gratitude, we will provide you with a subdomain, similar to pwnwriter.nixthe.systems. Thank you for your support!\nReach out\nFeel free to dm me at x.com/pwnwriter or mail at pwnwriter@nixthe.systems.\n\n    \n\n","id":"https://nixthe.systems/about/","title":"Nix The Systems"},"https://nixthe.systems/configurations/":{"body":"","id":"https://nixthe.systems/configurations/","title":"Configurations"},"https://nixthe.systems/docs/":{"body":"This is Nix The system’s blog index. Here, you’ll find all the latest updates, insights, documentations and announcements about Nix The Systems.\n","id":"https://nixthe.systems/docs/","title":"Nix The Systems"},"https://nixthe.systems/docs/installing-nixos-on-vps/":{"body":"\n\nIn this guide, we’ll walk you through the process of installing NixOS on a\nVirtual Private Server (VPS).\nWhile most VPS providers don’t offer Nix as a default OS installation option,\nthere is a workaround using nixos-anywhere. In this post, I’ll walk you\nthrough how to install NixOS on any VPS.\n\nPS: Example is a hetzner vps, already running an ubuntu iso.\n\nHow\nKexec is a system call that allows you to load and boot into a new kernel\ndirectly from the currently running kernel. We will use it to boot into our\nminimal install system without needing a flash drive. Additionally,\nnixos-anywhere allows us to automatically format and\npartition using disko declaratively, and install the OS.\nRequirements:\n\nA nix(os) system\nRoot access over the server\n1 gigs of RAM\n1 cores of cpu\n\nConfiguration\nWe’ll be using flakes to define our overall nixos config.\nThe file tree structure should look like this below.\n\n\nflake.lock is similar to cargo.lock, package.json, lazy-lock.json it locks the package git rev hash.\nconfiguration.nix is used to define our configuration for the nixos.\ndisk-config.nix is to define our disko config\n\nThe initial flake.nix skeleton look like this\n\nInside flake.nix, we’ll add our input repository url, nixpkgs and disko.\n\nand then we’ll define our output  servers. For this example, i’m using my\nserver name as wolf, you can name yours anything.\n\n\nMy server is x86_64-linux you’ll want to change that accordingly.\n\nI’m using the default example disk config from disko. It’ll create boot\nand root partitions. I also recommend using the default unless you explicitly\nwant to change. You’ll want to change the device name, to know run $ lsblk \n\ndisk-config.nix\n\n\nNow the configuration part.\n\nconfiguration.nix\n\nWe’ll first import qemu-guest module since it’s a virtual machine.\n\nI’ll be using grub as bootloader.\n\nOpenssh is necessary for us to be able to ssh into the new server.\n\nYou can define aditional packages to install as follows.\n\nNow, our final configuration.nix should look like this.\n\nInstall the os\nNow, we’ll have to run our flake to install nixos on the vps.\n\nIt’ll ask for the root password on installation.\n\n\nCongratulations!! The nixos has been installed successfully. You should be able to just edit the configuration and run\n\nthe other time on any changes.\nAditional tips…\nYou can use justfile to make this script running easy\n\nThe recipe should look like this\n\nNow, rebuild the os with just r(ebuild)\nWell, it’s this for now, I’ll see you in the next one!\n\n","id":"https://nixthe.systems/docs/installing-nixos-on-vps/","title":"Install NixOS on any VPS"}},"docInfo":{"https://nixthe.systems/":{"body":8,"title":1},"https://nixthe.systems/about/":{"body":81,"title":2},"https://nixthe.systems/configurations/":{"body":0,"title":1},"https://nixthe.systems/docs/":{"body":14,"title":2},"https://nixthe.systems/docs/installing-nixos-on-vps/":{"body":256,"title":3}},"length":5},"lang":"English"}